{"description": "Detects the usage of \"mstsc.exe\" with the \"/v\" flag to initiate a connection to a remote server.\nAdversaries may use valid accounts to log into a computer using the Remote Desktop Protocol (RDP). The adversary may then perform actions as the logged-on user.\n", "author": ["frack113"], "enabled": false, "false_positives": ["WSL (Windows Sub System For Linux)"], "filters": [], "from": "now-360s", "immutable": false, "index": ["winlogbeat-*"], "interval": "5m", "rule_id": "954f0af7-62dd-418f-b3df-a84bc2c7a774", "language": "lucene", "max_signals": 100, "risk_score": 35, "name": "New Remote Desktop Connection Initiated Via Mstsc.EXE", "query": "((((process.executable.text:\"*\\\\mstsc.exe\") OR (winlog.event_data.OriginalFileName:\"mstsc.exe\")) AND process.command_line.text:\"*\\ \\/v\\:*\") AND (NOT (process.parent.executable.text:\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\lxss\\wslhost.exe\" AND process.command_line.text:\"*C\\:\\\\ProgramData\\\\Microsoft\\\\WSL\\\\wslg.rdp*\")))", "meta": {"from": "1m"}, "severity": "medium", "tags": ["Lateral Movement", "T1021"], "to": "now", "type": "query", "threat": [{"tactic": {"id": "TA0008", "reference": "https://attack.mitre.org/tactics/TA0008", "name": "Lateral Movement"}, "framework": "MITRE ATT&CK", "technique": [{"id": "T1021", "name": "Remote Services", "reference": "https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1021"}]}], "version": 1, "references": ["https://github.com/redcanaryco/atomic-red-team/blob/f339e7da7d05f6057fdfcdd3742bfcf365fee2a9/atomics/T1021.001/T1021.001.md#t1021001---remote-desktop-protocol", "https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/administration/windows-commands/mstsc"], "license": "https://github.com/Neo23x0/sigma/blob/master/LICENSE.Detection.Rules.md", "timestamp_override": "event.ingested"}
